OL,5, A UK subsidiary of mining giant        
OL,6, Glencore has been ordered to pay more  
OL,7, than #275m for bribing officials in    
OL,8, African countries to get access to oil.
OL,10,FThe company paid $26m (#23m) through   
OL,11,Fagents and employees to officials of   
OL,12,Fcrude oil firms in Nigeria, Cameroon   
OL,13,Fand Ivory Coast between 2011 and 2016. 
OL,15,FProsecutors said Glencore Energy UK    
OL,16,Femployees and agents used private jets 
OL,17,Fto transfer cash to pay the bribes.    
OL,19,FGlencore Energy UK pleaded guilty to   
OL,20,Fseven corruption offences in June.     
